    "en": {
      "title": "A birth at the passport office",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A pregnant mother who was waiting in the queue to get passports at the main office of the Immigration Department in Battaramulla gave birth to a child early today (7).",
        "An officer of the Immigration Department said that the 26-year-old mother and child residing in the Hatton area are currently in very good health at Borella Castle Hospital and when she was in labor pain while waiting in the queue, the army officers intervened and admitted her to the hospital."
      ],
